  "tips": [
    "The Higuer lighthouse, which takes its name from the cape where it is located, illuminates the sea from this beautiful location, between the mouth of the Bidasoa and Mount Jaizkibel.\r\nIt was built in 1881.",
    "It is a beautiful coastal path between cliffs and rocky coves. The intense green color of the grass that covers the cliffs contrasts with the blue of the Cantabrian Sea: the classic picture of the spectacular Basque coast.",
    "Among the cove a quiet place for a dip and read a book.",
    "There are several paths that reach the Higuer lighthouse. There is an option which is to take the one that runs along the coast, although this one, which runs inland, is also very attractive and you will be surrounded by trees most of the time, so in autumn a nice blanket of leaves forms. ."
